@startuml 16.6_filterCommentBlog
hide footbox
title Filter Comment Post

actor User as "Users"
boundary CommentPostPage as View
control CommentPostRoute as Route
participant ":AuthMiddleware" as Middleware
control "CommentPostController" as Controller
participant ":CommentPostService" as Service
participant ":CommentPostModel" as Model
database Database as Database

User -> View : 1. Select filter options\n(keyword, status)
activate View
activate User

    View -> Route : 3. GET /api/v1/comment?keyword=&status=&page=&size=
    activate Route

    Route -> Middleware : 4. AuthenticateUser(req, res, next)
    activate Middleware
    ref over User, Database : Verifies token
    Middleware -> Controller : 5. Forward FilterCommentBlogRequest(params)
    deactivate Middleware
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Service : 6. Process comment filtering
    activate Service

    Service -> Model : 7. Build filter criteria
    activate Model

    Model -> Database : 8. Retrieve filtered comment data
    activate Database
    Database --> Model : 9. Result set
    deactivate Database

    Model --> Service : 10. Return filtered list + paging info
    deactivate Model

alt No comments match
    Service --> Controller : 11.1. Return empty result
    Controller --> Route : 11.1.1. Return 200 OK + empty list/message
    Route --> View : 11.1.2. Show "No comments found" + keep filters
else Comments match
    Service --> Controller : 11.2. Return FilterCommentBlogResponse
    deactivate Service
    Controller --> Route : 11.2.1. Return 200 OK + filtered comments data
    deactivate Controller
    Route --> View : 11.2.2. Render filtered list + pagination
    deactivate Route
end

View --> User : 12. Display filter result
deactivate View
deactivate User
@enduml
